## 5. Propshaft (Asset Pipeline)

Propshaft is the new default asset pipeline in Rails 8, replacing Sprockets.

### Key Differences from Sprockets

- **Simpler** - Focused on serving static assets
- **No compilation** - Use modern JS tools (esbuild) if needed
- **Faster** - Optimized for speed
- **Asset fingerprinting** - Automatic cache busting
- **Smaller codebase** - Easier to maintain

### Directory Structure

```
app/
├── assets/
│   ├── stylesheets/
│   │   └── application.tailwind.css
│   └── images/
│       ├── logo.png
│       └── hero.jpg
└── javascript/
    ├── application.js
    └── controllers/
```

### Asset Helpers

```erb
<!-- Images -->
<%= image_tag "logo.png", alt: "Logo" %>

<!-- Stylesheets (auto-loaded) -->
<%= stylesheet_link_tag "application", "data-turbo-track": "reload" %>

<!-- JavaScript (auto-loaded) -->
<%= javascript_importmap_tags %>
```

### Asset Fingerprinting

```
# Development
/assets/logo.png

# Production (fingerprinted for cache busting)
/assets/logo-a1b2c3d4e5f6.png
```

### Commands

```bash
# Precompile for production
rails assets:precompile

# Clean compiled assets
rails assets:clobber
```
